-- Jupiter Fund Management assets hit record 33.1 bln stg in June quarter
-- By Nishant Kumar
-- Wed Jul 30, 2014 02:34AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, July 30 (Reuters) - Jupiter Fund Management <JUP.L> said funds under management (FuM) rose to a record 33.1 billion pounds ($56.08 billion) in the June quarter, boosted by inflows into its fixed income products.

The money manager, which started the year with 31.7 billion pounds in assets, took a net 875 million pounds into its mutual funds during the quarter, it said in a statement. The company reported a pretax profit of 48.4 million pounds and said it had maintained its operating margins above 50 percent. It also announced an interim dividend of 3.7 pence as part of a progressive dividend policy. Jupiter said roughly three quarters of the assets in its mutual funds had delivered first and second quartile investment performance,